table.title: List of busiest railway stations in North America - List of busiest railway stations by annual passenger and commuter rail volume

query: Please provide the passenger volume ranking, main services, and interchange systems for railway stations located in Chicago.
summary: Chicago Union Station ranks 5th in passenger volume with 43.948 million annual entries/exits, and its main services are Amtrak and Metra, with interchanges to Chicago "L." Ogilvie Transportation Center comes in 6th place with 31.905 million passengers, primarily serving Metra and connecting to the Chicago "L." Lastly, Millennium Station ranks 13th with 10.764 million passengers, primarily serving Metra and also having interchanges with the Chicago "L."
